s 42P01.","Applied the product_master DDL, verified grants, and reran the product load. The final fix should verify the target schema, table owner, indexes, and grants before enabling the DAG schedule. Add a pre-flight task that calls to_regclass for product_master and fails with a clear deployment message if the object is missing. Once DDL is applied, rerun the failed task and confirm product_master is accessible to the Airflow role.","The product master refresh was blocked for all feeds using the target table. The incident affected platform reliability for product data processing, which can block multiple feeds or repeated reruns until the environment issue is corrected. Downstream systems may continue operating on stale product_master data while the platform incident remains open. Given priority P1, the support team should check whether other product DAGs failed in the same window.","Add a table existence pre-flight check and include product_master DDL in deployment migration validation. Add deployment gates that verify product_master exists before enabling the DAG. Include table existence, grants, indexes, and ownership checks in the release pipeline. The DAG should fail fast with a deployment-specific message when pre-flight checks fail. Add an audit record for every run containing dag_id, task_id, run_id, source file checksum, row count, validation status, and final product_master reconciliation. Feed these fields into the RAG knowledge base so future AutoRCA can distinguish data defects, platform defects, and SLA defects without relying on a single log line.",N,91,14,6.50,,,not_started_database_precheck,0,1,target_table_missing,,8GB,4GB,32MB,Y,,
