ed product identifier is not isolated, and the SQLSTATE or equivalent diagnostic code is 42501.","Granted INSERT, SELECT, and UPDATE privileges to the Airflow role and reran the failed task. The final fix should restore the least-privilege grants required by the load and export tasks, then validate them using the same Airflow connection used at runtime. Do not rely only on manual database console testing with an administrator role. After grants are corrected, rerun the task and record the grant validation in the incident notes.","The product load was blocked even though the source feed was valid. The incident affected platform reliability for product data processing, which can block multiple feeds or repeated reruns until the environment issue is corrected. Downstream systems may continue operating on stale product_master data while the platform incident remains open. Given priority P1, the support team should check whether other product DAGs failed in the same window.","Validate database grants during deployment and monitor critical ETL role privileges. Manage grants as code and validate privileges using the exact Airflow runtime role. Monitor privilege drift on product_master and alert when required INSERT, SELECT, or UPDATE grants are missing. Include grant checks in every environment refresh. Add an audit record for every run containing dag_id, task_id, run_id, source file checksum, row count, validation status, and final product_master reconciliation. Feed these fields into the RAG knowledge base so future AutoRCA can distinguish data defects, platform defects, and SLA defects without relying on a single log line.",N,6200,8,775.00,,,not_started_database_precheck,0,2,database_privilege_issue,INC022,4GB,4GB,32MB,Y,,
