ile retransmission, validated checksum, and reran the DAG. The file should be retransmitted or restored to the expected location, then validated for checksum, timestamp, and row count before the load starts. The DAG should use a file sensor rather than failing immediately when upstream delivery is delayed. The incident should close only after the product_master load completes using the exact file version approved by the source owner.","The daily product refresh could not start until the source file was delivered. The affected product feed did not complete successfully for task load_vendor_product_feed in DAG retail_product_master_daily_load, so product_master could remain stale or partially unreconciled until rerun. Downstream catalog, pricing, search, inventory, and analytics consumers should be checked for stale data exposure. The impact window starts at 2026-01-09 09:58:00 and ends only after the corrected run is validated.","Use a file sensor with SLA alerting and checksum validation before the load task starts. Use file sensors, source SLA alerts, and checksum validation before the load task. Separate source delivery incidents from database load incidents so the RCA does not blame product_master when no database activity occurred. Track expected and actual file arrival timestamps. Add an audit record for every run containing dag_id, task_id, run_id, source file checksum, row count, validation status, and final product_master reconciliation. Feed these fields into the RAG knowledge base so future AutoRCA can distinguish data defects, platform defects, and SLA defects without relying on a single log line.",Y,1204,3,401.33,,,postgres_copy_staging,50000,1,source_file_missing,,16GB,8GB,32MB,Y,,
