mary error was DataQualityException: selling_price cannot be lower than cost_price; offending product_id=6204, cost_price=44999.00, selling_price=39999.00. The extracted product identifier is 6204, and the SQLSTATE or equivalent diagnostic code is not applicable.","Corrected the promotional price in PricingERP, regenerated the product price feed, and reran the validation and load tasks. The fix should correct the business data at the source and rerun validation before loading product_master. Do not bypass the rule unless an approved business exception exists, because the rejected data could produce incorrect catalog, inventory, or pricing behavior. After rerun, confirm that the offending product_id is either corrected in product_master or intentionally excluded with audit evidence.","Product price updates were blocked to prevent negative margin exposure in customer-facing channels. The task failure protected downstream systems from receiving invalid product records. Although the load delay is visible to business users, allowing the bad data through could have caused incorrect pricing, invalid inventory display, or wrong product status. The impact should therefore be tracked as both a delayed refresh and a prevented data-quality escape.","Add source-side validation that selling_price must be greater than or equal to cost_price unless an approved markdown exception exists. Keep business-rule validation explicit and version controlled. Report rejected product_id values with reason codes so business teams can correct source data quickly. Measure prevented data-quality escapes as a positive control, not only as failed loads. Add an audit record for every run containing dag_id, task_id, run_id, source file checksum, row count, validation status, and final product_master reconciliation. Feed these fields into the RAG knowledge base so future AutoRCA can distinguish data defects, platform defects, and SLA defects without relying on a single log line.",Y,185000,49,3775.51,,,