: deadlock detected while merging product_master; SQLSTATE=40P01. The extracted product identifier is not isolated, and the SQLSTATE or equivalent diagnostic code is 40P01.","Cancelled the lower-priority merge, reran it after the first transaction completed, and changed the merge scheduler to serialize overlapping product_id ranges. The final fix should remove the blocking transaction, rerun the merge after locks clear, and inspect pg_locks or deadlock details to identify the conflicting process. Recurring jobs should be rescheduled or serialized where they touch overlapping product_id ranges. After rerun, validate that no partial transaction remains and that product_master row counts reconcile.","Omnichannel product updates were delayed for stores and ecommerce channels until the merge completed successfully. The incident affected platform reliability for product data processing, which can block multiple feeds or repeated reruns until the environment issue is corrected. Downstream systems may continue operating on stale product_master data while the platform incident remains open. Given priority P1, the support team should check whether other product DAGs failed in the same window.","Add advisory locks or range-based serialization for concurrent product_master merge tasks. Add lock checks before large merges and serialize jobs that update overlapping product_id ranges. Use advisory locks or a scheduler-level mutual exclusion policy for product_master merge tasks. Monitor lock wait time and deadlock counts as leading indicators. Add an audit record for every run containing dag_id, task_id, run_id, source file checksum, row count, validation status, and final product_master reconciliation. Feed these fields into the RAG knowledge base so future AutoRCA can distinguish data defects, platform defects, and SLA defects without relying on a single log line.",Y,342000,401,852.87,,,staging_table_merge,100000,2,database_deadlock_during_merge,INC017,8GB,4GB,128MB,N,57.00,57.0